<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 26 日星期五 07:16:44 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Twitter Engineering Chief ‘Leaves the Nest’ After Ron DeSantis’ Glitchy Presidential Launch]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110598114" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110597957_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_60ab7283f67c83ba9af588cacc508f1b.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110597939" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/twitter-engineering-chief-leaves-the-nest-after-ron-desantis-glitchy-presidential-launch-1110598114.html?share-img=1110597939"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / CONSTANZA HEVIA</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2022 年 10 月 28 日，加利福尼亚州旧金山 Twitter 总部外部的标志上可以看到 Twitter 徽标</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="The Twitter logo is seen on a sign on the exterior of Twitter headquarters in San Francisco, California, on October 28, 2022 - Sputnik International, 1920, 26.05.2023" title="2022 年 10 月 28 日，在加利福尼亚州旧金山的 Twitter 总部外部的标志上可以看到 Twitter 徽标" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110597957_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_8bf8537c81e6f27ea4efabf7d3387601.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110597957_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_331eeb345ff2b0b0d03fc7a0fbba98c1.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110597957_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_7c6879bd9b4eb2da1bcb2e458a0c7a3c.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110597957_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_8bf8537c81e6f27ea4efabf7d3387601.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / CONSTANZA HEVIA </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Oleg Burunov - Sputnik International" title="奥列格布鲁诺夫" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/09/0b/1080424846_0:0:2048:2048_100x100_80_0_0_3d7b461f8a98586fa3fe739930816aea.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">奥列格布鲁诺夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_burunov_oleg/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:o.burunov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">这位佛罗里达州州长在推特上的 2024 年总统竞选活动于周三晚上因技术故障而拉开序幕，这促使数十万用户当时离开了该平台。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Twitter 的工程主管 Foad Dabiri 宣布他将辞职，此举是在该平台软盘发布佛罗里达州州长<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/ron-desantis-no-match-for-trump-in-republican-presidential-primary-race-1110583864.html" target="_blank">罗恩德桑蒂斯的总统竞选</a>公告后的第二天。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “在 Twitter 度过了近四年令人难以置信的岁月之后，我昨天决定离开家。梦幻般的社区、它所具有的影响以及它无限的潜力的结合使 Twitter 与众不同，”Dabiri 周五在推特上<a href="https://twitter.com/foaddabiri/status/1661817359580147712?s=20" target="_blank">写道</a>。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110598114" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/twitter-engineering-chief-leaves-the-nest-after-ron-desantis-glitchy-presidential-launch-1110598114.html?share-block=1110598264" data-title="“After almost four incredible years at Twitter, I decided to leave the nest yesterday. The combination of the fantastic community, the impact it has, and its limitless potential sets Twitter apart,” Dabiri tweeted on Friday."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他承认， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230511/elon-musk-reveals-new-twitter-ceo-will-take-over-post-in-six-weeks-1110272648.html" target="_blank">埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk)</a>于 2022 年 10 月收购了 Twitter，这让工作变得“充满挑战”，伴随着大量“外部噪音”，但这对情况产生了积极影响。据 Dabiri 说，他从这次经历中学到了很多东西。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他没有具体说明他决定离开 Twitter 的原因，以及是否与德桑蒂斯总统竞选活动相关的问题有关。推特尚未就达比里的辞职一事发表评论。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他发表上述言论之前，德桑蒂斯周三参加白宫竞选时因推特直播<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/florida-governor-ron-desantis-announces-2024-presidential-election-campaign-1110571472.html" target="_blank">出现故障</a>而遇到问题。美国媒体报道称，最初有 50 万人登录观看，但当活动在暂停 20 分钟后最终开始时，只剩下一半人数。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">马斯克和主持人大卫萨克斯坚持认为问题是由于“服务器压力”和“服务器融化”造成的，因为德桑蒂斯竞标据称是有史以来最大的在线活动。就特斯拉和 SpaceX 的老板而言，他后来试图一笑置之，发推文称“今日地球上的头条新闻”。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110598114" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/twitter-engineering-chief-leaves-the-nest-after-ron-desantis-glitchy-presidential-launch-1110598114.html?share-block=1110598266" data-title="Musk along with moderator David Sacks insisted that the problems were due to “server strain” and “melting the servers,” because the DeSantis bid purportedly was the largest event ever hosted online. The Tesla and SpaceX boss, for his part, later tried to laugh off the lapse, tweeting about “top story on Earth today.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">以<strong>440 亿美元</strong>收购 Twitter 的马斯克上个月告诉一家英国新闻媒体，将公司的员工人数从他收购公司时的约<strong>8,000 人</strong>削减至约 2,000 人并不容易。被解雇的员工包括数十名负责 Twitter 网站运营和技术故障排除的工程师。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与此同时，德桑蒂斯竞选团队宣布，尽管 Twitter 事件充满了故障，这位佛罗里达州州长还是在他成为总统候选人的头 24 小时内成功筹集了高达<strong>820 万美元的</strong>资金。相比之下， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230418/trumps-presidential-campaign-hauls-in-over-15-million-in-post-indictment-donations-1109621210.html" target="_blank">美国前总统唐纳德·特朗普</a>在 2022 年 11 月中旬宣布参选 2024 年入主白宫后的六周内筹集了约<strong>950 万美元</strong>。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 26 May 2023 06:18:41 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230526/twitter-engineering-chief-leaves-the-nest-after-ron-desantis-glitchy-presidential-launch-1110598114.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230526/twitter-engineering-chief-leaves-the-nest-after-ron-desantis-glitchy-presidential-launch-1110598114.html<category>世界</category><category>我们</category><category>推特</category><category>埃隆·马斯克</category><category>罗恩德桑蒂斯</category><category>总统竞选</category><category>辞职</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Norway Setting Up New Radar Chain Dubbed 'NATO's Eyes in the North']]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110597542" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103876/02/1038760265_0:0:2690:1473_1440x900_80_0_1_4f9172952b602b6ff90929e69bb99c23.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1038760264" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/norway-setting-up-new-radar-chain-dubbed-natos-eyes-in-the-north-1110597542.html?share-img=1038760264"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / Pierre-Henry DESHAYES /</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Globus II 雷达站出现在挪威北部的 Vardoe</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="Globus II Radar stations are seen in Vardoe, northern Norway - Sputnik International, 1920, 26.05.2023" title="挪威北部 Vardoe 的 Globus II 雷达站" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103876/02/1038760265_0:0:2619:1473_1920x0_80_0_0_eb5dd6ec15078d5367a6277c85c11b00.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103876/02/1038760265_0:0:2619:1473_640x0_80_0_0_a2e6ebb711748561772a07332c3fc4f0.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103876/02/1038760265_0:0:2619:1473_1280x0_80_0_0_83ec7d37225db5be3f0161075d1efa4e.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103876/02/1038760265_0:0:2619:1473_1920x0_80_0_0_eb5dd6ec15078d5367a6277c85c11b00.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / Pierre-Henry DESHAYES / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊戈尔·库兹涅佐夫</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_kuznetsov_igor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">整个挪威正在建设的由八个雷达组成的新网络被吹捧为扩大对挪威和周边领空的持续监视范围的手段，包括代表北约联盟。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">挪威国防财产局 (NDEA) 是国防部下属的一个政府机构，它已经提交了雷达链的建设计划，旨在增强挪威自身的无线电能力，进而增强北约的无线电能力。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">作为该国雷达网络大幅升级的一部分，议会委托新链中的第一个设施将于 2025 年秋季在奥斯陆北部 Ringerike 市的 Gyrihaugen 建造，相关工作已经在进行中。热门旅游景点 Gyrihaugen 山的斜坡今年冬天因施工而关闭。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “NDEA 将在全国建造总共八个新雷达。新雷达系统将有助于加强挪威的防御能力，并成为北约在北方的眼睛，”项目负责人 Ylva Sneve 说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110597542" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/norway-setting-up-new-radar-chain-dubbed-natos-eyes-in-the-north-1110597542.html?share-block=1110597545" data-title="&quot;NDEA is to build a total of eight new radars across the country. The new radar systems will help to strengthen Norway's defense capability, and be NATO's eyes in the north,&quot; project leader Ylva Sneve said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">总的来说，武装部队将投资 80 亿挪威克朗（7.2 亿美元）用于从南部的 Ringerike 到北部的 Vardo 的八个新<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/uk-norway-launch-strategic-partnership-in-undersea-domain-1110453810.html" target="_blank">雷达系统</a>，这些雷达系统由该国空军运营。其中五个将建在新地点，而三个现有雷达站将进行大幅升级。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">挪威国防部在一份新闻稿中表示，结合战斗机和地面防空系统的使用，它确保了挪威领空的安全，并加强了其军队的行动自由。据称，新雷达将使挪威武装部队能够持续监视挪威和周边领空。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “飞机、导弹和无人机已成为现代战争的重要组成部分。因此，拥有能够监控这一领域的系统至关重要。不仅是为了我们自己，也是为了我们在北约的盟友。这些新雷达将提高我们的观点范围相当大，”国防部长比约恩·阿里尔德·格拉姆在此前的一份声明中说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110597542" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/norway-setting-up-new-radar-chain-dubbed-natos-eyes-in-the-north-1110597542.html?share-block=1110597548" data-title="&amp;quot;Airplanes, missiles, and drones have become an important part of modern warfare. It is therefore of the utmost importance to have systems that can monitor this domain. Not only for ourselves, but also for our allies in NATO. These new radars will improve the range of our view considerably,&amp;quot; Defense Minister Bjorn Arild Gram said in a previous statement."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2022 年，时任国防部长弗兰克·巴克-詹森承认，当今的大部分雷达“正在<strong>迅速接近使用寿命终点</strong>”，必须更新换代以迎接未来的挑战。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">为什么挪威的雷达如此重要？</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2022 年 11 月，挪威国防物资局 (NDMA) 与<a href="https://sputniknews.com/organization_Lockheed_Martin/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">洛克希德·马丁公司</a>签订了一份合同，交付 8 台空域监视雷达，并可选择额外增加 3 台雷达。根据合同，将建立三个区域技术维护中心来监测传感器的状况。雷达的交付将于 2030 年完成。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">世界上最大的军舰杰拉尔德福特号航空母舰最近在其首次作战航行期间停靠奥斯陆港口，突显了美国和挪威之间的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/needing-us-hires-norway-dubs-lack-of-f-35-mechanics-declaration-of-bankruptcy-1110362342.html" target="_blank">密切合作</a>。挪威官员称这次港口停靠是“通过北约明确表达安全保证”。美国驻挪威大使马克·内森森强调了挪威作为创始成员<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230503/norway-pledges-to-reach-natos-spending-target-amid-windfall-revenues-1110046404.html" target="_blank">在该联盟中的作用</a>，并将其描述为美国在北欧地区的“首选”合作伙伴。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">其中，挪威拥有广泛的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20200506/a-threat-to-the-town-norwegians-protest-against-us-arctic-radar-upgrade-1079210126.html" target="_blank">Globus 雷达系统</a>。虽然它是由挪威情报局在空间观测和<a href="https://sputniknews.com/tag_Arctic/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">北极</a>空域监测的前提下为挪威国家利益正式运营的，但该站点靠近<a href="https://sputniknews.com/geo_Russia/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">俄罗斯</a>北方舰队及其在<a href="https://sputniknews.com/geo_Kola_Peninsula/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">科拉半岛</a>的海军基地，以及广泛参与建设和资金，导致假设它也作为美国导弹防御系统的一部分。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 26 May 2023 06:17:13 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230526/norway-setting-up-new-radar-chain-dubbed-natos-eyes-in-the-north-1110597542.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230526/norway-setting-up-new-radar-chain-dubbed-natos-eyes-in-the-north-1110597542.html<category>军队</category><category>挪威</category><category>奥斯陆</category><category>北约</category><category>我们</category><category>雷达</category><category>斯堪的纳维亚</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biting Back at China over Micron Will Break US’ Teeth]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110598466" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/01/1100260807_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_c8d5049967fa3dc96207d6e3fdd35c9b.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1100260789" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/biting-back-at-china-over-micron-will-break-us-teeth-1110598466.html?share-img=1100260789"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Patrick Semansky</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2022 年 3 月 9 日，总统乔·拜登在华盛顿白宫南法院礼堂出席支持鼓励国内制造和加强计算机芯片供应链的立法活动。就在参议院共和党领袖米奇麦康奈尔威胁要阻止一项重振美国计算机芯片行业的法案前几个小时，拜登的高级助手于周四上午举行会议，为这种情况制定计划。他们决定继续推动和努力与立法者建立超过 18 个月的两党关系，最终通过了价值 2800 亿美元的 CHIPS 和科学法案。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="President Joe Biden attends an event to support legislation that would encourage domestic manufacturing and strengthen supply chains for computer chips in the South Court Auditorium on the White House campus, March 9, 2022, in Washington. Just hours before Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell threatened to block a bill to revive the U.S. computer chip sector, senior Biden aides met on a Thursday morning to plan for that exact scenario. They decided to keep pushing and working bipartisan relationships with legislators developed over 18 months, leading to the passage of the $280 billion CHIPS and Science Act. - Sputnik International, 1920, 26.05.2023" title="2022 年 3 月 9 日，总统乔·拜登 (Joe Biden) 在白宫南法院礼堂出席支持鼓励国内制造和加强计算机芯片供应链的立法活动。就在参议院共和党领袖米奇麦康奈尔威胁要阻止一项重振美国计算机芯片行业的法案的几个小时前，拜登的高级助手于周四上午开会，为这种情况制定计划。他们决定继续推动和努力与立法者建立超过 18 个月的两党关系，最终通过了价值 2800 亿美元的 CHIPS 和科学法案。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/01/1100260807_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_8c56868051685fe609092d64c4398afa.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/01/1100260807_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_e0255d9bb6cd76a2dba6303fe5b30694.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/01/1100260807_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_4264eecc05c222f93ac5cd49a0f3aa39.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/01/1100260807_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_8c56868051685fe609092d64c4398afa.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Patrick Semansky </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">美光在中国销售的产品未通过网络安全审查的消息在美国引起强烈反响。这间接表明，中国的决定触动了一些美国人，显示了它的力量并产生了额外的影响。但是，事情的真相是美方无法掩盖的。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国商务部发言人在一份声明中表示，这是对美国公司的“突袭和攻击”，“没有事实依据”的限制将导致“存储芯片市场的扭曲”。这是华盛顿一贯使用强硬的言词为其行动辩护。事实上，这些话不过是用来形容美国近年来破坏自由贸易行为的词组而已。但中国不是美国，不会向华盛顿学习不良行为。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这一结论是经过中国海关总署长达七周的调查，以及中国网络安全审查办公室（CRO）依法进行的网络安全审查后得出的，经得起推敲。审查发现，美光产品存在严重网络安全隐患，对我国关键信息基础设施供应链构成重大安全风险，影响我国国家安全。根据国家《网络安全法》等法律法规，中国关键信息基础设施运营商应停止采购美光产品。<br><br>除了评估中国的决定会给美光带来多大损失，美方也表现出一定程度的不安和不安全感，认为“此事的爆炸半径可能要大得多”。这主要是因为他们对中国做了很多无耻之事，非常清楚美国打着“国家安全”的幌子攻击中国企业意味着什么。因此，他们条件反射地认为，中国对美国企业采取的任何行动都是“报复”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当然，让那些损害中国利益的人感到不安并不是坏事，也是他们应得的惩罚。美光案确实是CRO首次对外国公司进行审查，但美光并不是第一家接受该办公室安全审查的公司。所谓“针对外企”根本不是事实。唯一说明的是，随着中国监管体系的逐步完善，所有市场主体在经营活动中都必须遵守中国法律。这与针对特定公司无关。不因企业“身份”不同而歧视，不针对任何人，不给予特殊待遇。<br><br>作为全球最大的半导体存储和影像产品制造商之一，美光在中国的产品长期以来一直被传存在网络安全风险。此外，美光一直以“咄咄逼人的竞争策略”着称于业界，被指在美国打压中国科技中扮演挑拨离间的角色，是在中国受到打击最多的美企。中国芯片企业。美光自己清楚自己是否与华盛顿合作，向中国出口不安全产品，而这无疑将决定其在中国市场的未来。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">多家外媒将此事纳入美中科技战范畴，暗示可能导致“科技战”升级。从表面上看，似乎是这样：以往在半导体领域，美国总是主动出击，而中国则受制于人，受制于人。现在，中国对美光出手了，展示了它的反击能力。然而，需要说明的是，事实并非如此。美国所谓的“国家安全”是对中国技术的单边反市场打压，而中国对美光的安全审查则是为了切实维护自身安全利益。两者的性质完全不同。华盛顿对中国的指责只能暴露其虚伪和双重标准。<br><br>其实，谁在无理打压、扭曲市场，世人早已一清二楚。中国刚刚开始审查美光时，白宫就要求韩国政府禁止韩国芯片制造商填补美光在中国市场留下的空白。就是这么霸道。多年来，面对华盛顿“小院子、高篱笆”战略和推动“脱钩”，中国始终坚持高水平开放，支持开放包容的世界经济秩序。这在相当程度上抵消了华盛顿带来的负面影响，极大地稳定了全球产业链和供应链。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">看看美国对华为的残酷无情打压，以及强行收购TikTok的贪婪和无法无天的企图。对自由贸易规则和公平竞争原则的践踏已经到了极端。而中方正当、必要的举动却被美方反过来反咬一口，更是心虚无理的表现。必须狠狠地揍他们一顿，让他们仔细权衡后果。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><em>本文首发于环球时报。</em></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 26 May 2023 06:15:32 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230526/biting-back-at-china-over-micron-will-break-us-teeth-1110598466.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230526/biting-back-at-china-over-micron-will-break-us-teeth-1110598466.html<category>世界</category><category>中国</category><category>美中关系</category><category>我们</category><category>筹码</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>环球时报</category></item></channel></rss>